  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2cbaeec8dbe84e069925173ac3a6210b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Dlg_Ruins_GM_Finale
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ElementalAlchemist.Dialogue.DialogueData
  _speaker: Grand Master
  _lines:
  - So. The Guardian gave up the last Fragment. I felt it the instant the Stone took shape; the whole realm leaned toward you.
  - You are my student no longer. From this moment you are a Master, my equal in every art that matters. I have waited my whole life to say that to anyone.
  - And now the work we were truly made for. At the Sanctuary, in the heart of these Ruins, stands the old altar where the three Fragments can be made one.
  - Carry Breath, Flesh, and Soul to the altar and fuse them. We will create Life itself, the final Element, the thing all of alchemy has only ever pointed toward.
  - This is why I raised you. Every realm, every trial, all of it for this. Go. I am right behind you, and after all these years, we finish it together.
